  "prompt": "How do I write scripts creatively?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help you write scripts creatively:\n\n1. Develop strong characters\n- Give characters clear motivations\n- Create unique personalities\n- Make characters complex and layered\n\n2. Start with a compelling premise\n- Have an interesting central conflict\n- Create a unique story hook\n- Think about what makes your story different\n\n3. Study script structure\n- Learn three-act structure\n- Understand plot progression\n- Study screenplay formatting\n\n4. Practice brainstorming techniques\n- Free writing\n- Mind mapping\n- Stream of consciousness writing\n\n5. Read and watch lots of scripts\n- Analyze successful screenplays\n- Study different genres\n- Learn storytelling techniques\n\n6. Develop your dialogue skills\n- Make conversations sound natural\n- Give each character a distinct voice\n- Use subtext and implied meaning\n\n7. Create engaging plot twists\n- Surprise the audience\n- Develop unexpected story developments\n- Maintain narrative tension\n\n8. Use writing prompts\n- Generate creative ideas\n- Challenge yourself with different scenarios\n- Experiment with various genres\n\n9. Write regularly\n- Set daily writing goals\n- Create a consistent writing routine\n- Don't self-edit during first drafts\n\n10. Get feedback\n- Join writing groups\n- Share your work\n- Be open to constructive criticism",
